      "span_text": "Even if the models are not explicitly included in a complete methodological framework, they still often assume a specific methodological approach. In particular, the requirements analysis phase can be based on approaches also common to conventional IS design, such as technical analysis, decision analysis, social or behavioral analysis, and prototype implementation for experimention [CITATION_1] ; correspondingly, some elements in the models are emphasized more than others."
